From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kanaka Raju Nayana <kanaka.raju.nayana@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 21:37:52 +0530
Subject: xe/gsc: include linux/random.h for get_random_bytes()

Build on 5.15 fails with implicit declaration of get_random_bytes() in
xe_gsc_submit.c due to missing direct prototype visibility.

Include linux/random.h in the Xe GSC submit source to get the declaration
without relying on fragile nested header inclusion.

Signed-off-by: Kanaka Raju Nayana <kanaka.raju.nayana@intel.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gsc_submit.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gsc_submit.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gsc_submit.c
index 9ede483..17cff2a 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gsc_submit.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gsc_submit.c
@@ -6,6 +6,7 @@
 #include "xe_gsc_submit.h"
 
 #include <linux/poison.h>
+#include <linux/random.h>
 
 #include "abi/gsc_command_header_abi.h"
 #include "xe_assert.h"
